The paper focuses on the performance of different schedulers in ultra dense small cell deployments, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the Rician fading channel model and the cross-correlation shadowing model, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The investigation of potential multi-user diversity gains is related to system and control (cs.SY), and the comparison of different schedulers is related to computer science and networking (cs.COM).
